Wow this was me same thing in US.  My primary had to refer me to women’s cancer center, did a mammogram 2 weeks later, waited a week for results, they wanted ultrasound, another 2 weeks to wait for appt, then they see a lump, schedule a biopsy 2 more weeks.  Oh and I was calling their billing dept and my insurance company throughout countless hours getting different answers if it would be covered or not under my plan. Also growing anxiety nervous it could be cancer. Finally about 2.5 mos after finding a lump got results it was a cyst!!! Unreal yet totally normal.. how?!
Fuck the USA.... It is a SHITHOLE in EVERY manner. What a fucking despicable Country!!!!

I am just being discharged from the premier cancer centre in West Australia as I type this. Sadly mine is malignant but treatment started the day I arrived, invoice for 10 days hospital care , meds, MRI, CT, X-RAY and MAMOGRAM,$0,  prepping for my 6  weeks out patient treatment, invoice $0, Travel to and from hospital each day I am paid 57¢ per km, overnight stay at a friend or family THEY are paid $20 per night for inconvenience, electricity water and internet, medications 6 taken twice daily = $0, radiotherapy chemo therapy and hormone therapy for 6 weeks to 12 weeks $0. All paid for thru my taxes, Cost of Universal Health care PRICELESS. 🙃🙃🙃😘

I shudder to think what would happen if I had a medical emergency!  I don’t have insurance.
.
My father had a heart attack and he was given two aspirins and sent home after a 6-hour wait in the emergency room.  He didn’t have insurance either.
.
I’ve met not one, but a handful of people who have lost their homes, cars and all worldly possessions because they had insurance, but the insurance either refused to pay, or didn’t pay enough.  Living in the US is like stepping over a mine field; you just never know when everything will implode right under your feet...
